==English==
===Pronunciation===
/beIt "nwA;, bEt, French bEt nwa1/
===Etymology===
The literal meaning of bête noire in French is "black beast."
===Noun===
'''[[bête]] [[noire]]''' (plural ''bêtes noires'', pronounced the same)
#An [[anathema]]; refers to someone or something which is particularly disliked or avoided; an object of aversion, the bane of one’s existence.

